WEBVTT

00:03.921 --> 00:04.910
NARRA TOR:
Previously on Heroes...

00:05.006 --> 00:06.291
I'll only be gone
for a while.

00:06.382 --> 00:08.293
This is your chance
at a normal life.

00:08.384 --> 00:10.170
Well, welcome
to New Orleans.

00:10.261 --> 00:11.376
Is that Pay-Per-View?

00:11.470 --> 00:14.086
Micah's some type of genius
and rigged the cable.

00:14.182 --> 00:15.171
(ANNOUNCER CHATTER/NG ON TV)

00:15.683 --> 00:17.139
I'll take everything
you got in the register.

00:17.226 --> 00:18.261
Okay.

00:18.352 --> 00:19.341
(GRUNTS)

00:22.565 --> 00:23.975
(HIRO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:29.780 --> 00:31.611
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:32.200 --> 00:34.191
(HIRO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:37.955 --> 00:41.197
You don't realize
how valued you are
here at the Company.

00:41.292 --> 00:42.702
You're part
of the family now.

00:42.793 --> 00:43.828
I'm in over
my head.

00:43.920 --> 00:46.081
As long as I'm alive,
you will be taken care of.

00:46.964 --> 00:48.875
CAITLIN: Peter!
This is everything
you had on you

00:48.966 --> 00:50.001
when we found you.

00:50.092 --> 00:52.549
Your box. Your life.
You gonna open it,
or what?

00:52.637 --> 00:55.344
Kaito Nakamura, murdered.
Angela Petrelli, attacked.

00:55.431 --> 00:57.217
This is my dad.
He may be the killer.

00:57.308 --> 00:58.388
I'll find your father.

00:58.476 --> 01:00.432
Molly, what's the
apartment number?

01:00.519 --> 01:01.770
Nine.
Nine. Good girl.

01:01.854 --> 01:03.355
All right, get out
of there, right now.
He sees me...

01:03.439 --> 01:04.599
Leave me alone!
Get out of there. Molly.

01:04.690 --> 01:07.181
No! No! No! Molly!
Please wake up.

01:08.402 --> 01:12.896
MOH/NDER: When confronted
by our worst nightmares,
the choices are few.

01:12.990 --> 01:15.481
Fight or flight.

01:16.410 --> 01:19.402
We hope to find the strength
to stand against our fears.

01:19.497 --> 01:22.159
But sometimes,
despite ourselves,
we run.

01:23.334 --> 01:25.791
What if the nightmare
gives chase?

01:26.295 --> 01:28.502
Where can we hide then?

01:28.756 --> 01:30.087
MATT: Okay. When
is she going
to wake up?

01:30.174 --> 01:31.914
I don't know.
She's burning up.

01:32.009 --> 01:33.465
All right, we gotta
get her to a hospital.

01:33.552 --> 01:35.804
No hospital is equipped
to deal with this.

01:35.888 --> 01:39.346
You really think
my father did this
to her in her nightmare?

01:39.642 --> 01:43.385
She used her ability
to find him for you
and slipped into this.

01:43.479 --> 01:45.811
(EXHALES)
She was so afraid.

01:47.108 --> 01:48.644
I never should've
asked her to look
for him.

01:48.734 --> 01:50.520
No, you shouldn't have.

01:50.611 --> 01:51.896
But now you know
where he is.

01:51.988 --> 01:53.444
I can't just
leave her like this.

01:53.531 --> 01:55.897
You have to.
If your father did
something to her,

01:55.992 --> 01:57.857
you need to find out
what and how to end it.

01:57.952 --> 02:00.819
You have an address
in Philadelphia.
She even saw his door.

02:02.206 --> 02:04.117
I haven't seen
the man in 25 years.

02:04.208 --> 02:06.540
Molly faced
her worst nightmare
for you.

02:06.627 --> 02:10.290
Do the same for her. Find him.
I'll stay here with her.
I'll do everything I can.

02:10.381 --> 02:12.463
I don't even know
what I'm dealing with.

02:12.550 --> 02:14.711
Why was he
in that photo?

02:16.887 --> 02:19.970
Angela Petrelli.
She knows him.

02:25.479 --> 02:27.561
You're going to be okay.

02:29.275 --> 02:31.311
(WHISPERS) I promise.

02:37.491 --> 02:39.948
l was about to lock up
when this guy showed up.

02:40.036 --> 02:43.028
He pushed his way in,
shoved a gun in my face.

02:43.122 --> 02:46.205
The next thing I know,
he's flying through
that glass.

02:46.292 --> 02:47.577
You hit an armed man?

02:49.045 --> 02:51.286
lguess.
It could've
been a kick.

02:51.380 --> 02:53.666
I don't know.
It all happened
so fast.

02:53.758 --> 02:55.794
Is this the guy?

03:00.973 --> 03:04.010
His name is Lonny Stills.
He's a local gang banger.

03:04.101 --> 03:07.059
He's already hit
three other fast-food joints
in the area this month.

03:07.146 --> 03:08.682
It fits his MO.

03:08.773 --> 03:10.638
Like I said,
it's all a blur.

03:10.733 --> 03:15.022
Look, I know you don't
want to be a snitch.
It's dangerous.

03:15.112 --> 03:16.727
But in order for me
to get this guy
off the street,

03:16.822 --> 03:20.110
I need somebody
to step up and ID him,
be a hero.

03:20.951 --> 03:24.159
I'm sorry.
I can't do that.

03:27.375 --> 03:31.084
You know,
I can't help a neighborhood
that won't help itself.

03:31.170 --> 03:34.128
You change your mind,
you give me a call.

03:41.305 --> 03:42.636
PETER: Closing up already?

03:43.933 --> 03:46.140
It's the middle
of the afternoon.

03:46.227 --> 03:48.263
I need a break.

03:55.319 --> 03:57.685
I could get
used to this.

03:57.780 --> 03:58.769
Right.

03:58.864 --> 04:01.731
A guy who can throw
a thousand volts
out of either hand

04:01.826 --> 04:04.863
settling for everyday
life in a pub in Cork?

04:04.954 --> 04:07.240
I'm not sure it suits you.

04:07.331 --> 04:09.037
Why not?

04:09.125 --> 04:11.241
Peter. Just because
you don't remember
your past,

04:11.502 --> 04:13.914
it doesn't mean
you don't have one.

04:14.004 --> 04:16.461
Aren't you curious
about who you are
or where you come from?

04:16.549 --> 04:18.710
You've seen what I can do.

04:18.801 --> 04:22.965
There's a side of me that
I can't control. Maybe it's
best if I don't dig too deep.

04:23.055 --> 04:26.343
I know the kind of man
you are, even if you don't.

04:26.434 --> 04:28.140
There's only good in you.

04:28.227 --> 04:31.219
And I bet whatever's
in that box will tell you
the same thing.

04:33.399 --> 04:36.857
Weren't you the one
who didn't want me
to look in that box?

04:36.944 --> 04:40.152
I only said that because
you hadn't kissed me yet.

04:43.159 --> 04:46.367
And now that you have,
you're done with me?

04:46.495 --> 04:48.531
(CHUCKLES)
Getting there.

04:51.041 --> 04:53.657
After all,
a pretty boy
like you,

04:53.752 --> 04:55.708
there's bound to be
someone looking for you.

04:55.796 --> 04:58.082
Friends,
a girlfriend.

05:00.759 --> 05:02.795
Let them look.

05:05.055 --> 05:06.636
(MEN CHATTERING)

05:06.724 --> 05:10.137
Like I told you,
you're not gonna
find him in there.

05:15.149 --> 05:17.640
But you're sure
it was him?

05:17.735 --> 05:21.398
Yeah. We found him
cuffed inside here
a few nights back.

05:21.489 --> 05:25.482
Poor sap didn't know
how he got there, didn't
even know his own name.

05:25.576 --> 05:27.362
Do you know
where he is now?

05:27.453 --> 05:28.659
Depends.

05:28.746 --> 05:30.737
Who's asking?

05:31.665 --> 05:33.656
Just me.

05:34.251 --> 05:37.994
I work for a company
interested in keeping
him out of trouble.

05:38.088 --> 05:40.750
Peter is a dangerous guy.

05:40.841 --> 05:44.299
(SCOFFS)
You don't have
to tell me that.

05:44.386 --> 05:45.762
He's in town.

05:45.846 --> 05:48.428
A place called
Wandering Rocks Pub.

05:50.100 --> 05:53.092
Hey, if he's
so dangerous,
sweetheart,

05:53.187 --> 05:56.475
why'd they send
a little girl like you
in all alone?

06:02.238 --> 06:04.274
I can take care
of myself.

06:25.886 --> 06:27.626
(MAN CHA TTER/NG
ON POL/CE RAD/O)

06:28.639 --> 06:30.425
Bring her back
to holding.

06:30.516 --> 06:31.631
What do you
think you're doing

06:31.725 --> 06:33.056
interrogating my mother
without me there?

06:33.143 --> 06:34.519
Relax. She didn't
give me anything.

06:34.603 --> 06:38.095
Of course she didn't
give you anything. These
people protect each other.

06:38.774 --> 06:39.889
My mother's not a killer.

06:39.984 --> 06:42.600
I'm not gonna have her
sit in jail for a crime
she didn't commit.

06:42.695 --> 06:45.027
Neither am |.
That's why I'm going
to Philadelphia.

06:45.114 --> 06:47.400
To see my father,
figure this whole thing out.

06:47.616 --> 06:48.605
Let me come with you.

06:48.701 --> 06:50.157
No. You're not a cop.

06:50.244 --> 06:53.077
Listen, I'm guessing
this isn't official
police business.

06:53.163 --> 06:54.949
So if I'm there,
it won't really
make a difference

06:55.040 --> 06:56.450
because officially
neither are you.

06:56.542 --> 06:59.409
You don't understand.
It's Molly. My father
did something to her.

06:59.503 --> 07:00.538
She's in trouble.

07:00.629 --> 07:01.789
What do you mean,
"did something to her"?

07:01.880 --> 07:03.256
Come here.

07:03.340 --> 07:04.375
Did What?

07:05.676 --> 07:07.337
He got inside
her head somehow.

07:07.469 --> 07:09.175
I don't know how
he did it, but I think
it's all connected.

07:09.263 --> 07:11.470
To Kaito, to your mother.

07:12.016 --> 07:13.927
It could be dangerous.

07:14.643 --> 07:16.679
I can take care of myself.

07:17.187 --> 07:19.348
Listen, l have
to do this.

07:20.858 --> 07:22.723
Let me come with you.

07:23.777 --> 07:28.111
Fine. We can probably
get there faster.
You know, 'cause you can...

07:29.241 --> 07:30.276
I'm not a cargo jet.

07:30.367 --> 07:31.447
(SIGHING) Please.

07:38.167 --> 07:40.249
RICKY: I need
to talk to him.

07:40.794 --> 07:42.785
Alone.

07:45.633 --> 07:47.715
Tell him
what you told me.

07:51.847 --> 07:55.089
This American girl
was hitting all the boys
on the dock

07:55.184 --> 07:58.142
is looking for
a certain
shipping container.

07:58.228 --> 07:59.604
She say what she wanted?

07:59.688 --> 08:01.849
Yeah. You.

08:10.699 --> 08:12.906
No worries, boyo.

08:12.993 --> 08:14.278
I think I can help.

08:14.370 --> 08:15.530
This is my problem.

08:15.621 --> 08:18.909
Not given what I just saw
between you and my sister.

08:20.000 --> 08:22.082
You care about her,
don't you?

08:22.169 --> 08:25.036
Right now she's the only
thing in my life
that means something.

08:25.130 --> 08:27.667
Caitlin has
a flat up
the hill.

08:27.758 --> 08:29.965
Go there and stay
until I call you.

08:30.052 --> 08:31.167
I'll take care of
your friend.

08:31.261 --> 08:33.172
I can handle this myself.

08:33.263 --> 08:36.050
I don't doubt it.
I've seen what you can do.

08:36.934 --> 08:39.266
But I've got
an investment
in you now,

08:39.353 --> 08:42.345
and some little blonde
isn't gonna scare me off.

08:43.399 --> 08:46.891
Now, go on,
and don't be telling
Caitlin about any of this.

08:46.985 --> 08:49.146
She'll only worry sick.

08:53.992 --> 08:56.028
Monica.

08:57.121 --> 08:59.157
Well?

08:59.248 --> 09:00.454
Well what?

09:00.541 --> 09:03.032
Well, are you gonna tell me
what that was all about?

09:03.127 --> 09:05.869
| just didn't want
some crack head
looking for revenge.

09:05.963 --> 09:07.169
So I said I didn't
recognize him.
No.

09:07.256 --> 09:11.670
No, not that. I'm talking
about the whole
flying-karate-kick thing.

09:12.052 --> 09:14.885
Oh. That.

09:14.972 --> 09:18.135
Mr. Lamont said
he has never seen
anything like it.

09:18.225 --> 09:20.432
How did you do that?

09:20.811 --> 09:24.474
More importantly,
why did you do that?

09:26.024 --> 09:27.730
I don't know.

09:27.818 --> 09:30.104
I don't know
anything anymore.

09:31.238 --> 09:33.524
Nothing makes any sense.

09:33.615 --> 09:37.733
Well, where did
you learn how to...

09:37.828 --> 09:41.161
lthink...
I think on TV.

09:45.169 --> 09:46.329
(SIGHING)

09:46.420 --> 09:49.583
Something is happening
to me, Camille.

09:49.673 --> 09:53.757
My body does things
before my brain even
knows what's happening.

09:54.511 --> 09:57.423
That thing with
the tomatoes yesterday...

09:57.514 --> 10:00.551
Now this. It's like...

10:01.518 --> 10:03.509
Like what?

10:04.146 --> 10:05.477
(SIGHING)

10:06.190 --> 10:08.772
l was supposed
to be somebody, Camille.

10:08.942 --> 10:12.309
The first person
in my family
to go to college.

10:14.281 --> 10:16.317
Now look at me.

10:18.368 --> 10:20.279
You know what? Never mind.

10:20.370 --> 10:23.328
I've been here since
last night. I'm just gonna
go home and sleep it off.

10:23.415 --> 10:27.658
Hey, Monica.
Everything's
gonna be okay.

10:30.714 --> 10:32.705
Okay?
Yeah.

10:34.384 --> 10:36.466
I hope so.

10:43.894 --> 10:45.759
All right, this is it.
This is where Molly
said we'd find him.

10:46.313 --> 10:47.894
What are you
planning exactly?

10:49.441 --> 10:50.476
(SIGHS)

10:50.567 --> 10:52.523
I'm not sure.
You're not sure.

10:52.611 --> 10:56.320
He's traumatized your girl.
Has my mother terrified.
You better get sure.

10:56.406 --> 10:58.818
Get your gun out.
Come on.

11:00.285 --> 11:02.321
Hey, are you okay?

11:02.621 --> 11:05.488
When lwas 13,
my father ran out on us.

11:05.582 --> 11:08.665
I haven't talked to him.
I haven't seen him.

11:08.752 --> 11:10.253
I spent half my life thinking
about what I'm gonna say

11:10.337 --> 11:13.420
to this guy if I ever got
the chance, and now I can't
even knock on the door.

11:19.096 --> 11:20.586
You're welcome.

11:20.681 --> 11:21.670
Parkman,
this is not
a family reunion.

11:21.765 --> 11:22.754
I know.

11:22.850 --> 11:26.809
Okay, he's not your dad
today. He's a suspect.
Get your gun out.

11:28.480 --> 11:30.562
Police! Open up.

11:31.275 --> 11:34.187
Who the hell are you?
I said, who the hell are you?

11:34.278 --> 11:35.688
Put the gun down
and I'll tell you.

11:35.779 --> 11:37.280
Parkman.

11:38.323 --> 11:40.109
Matt?

11:40.200 --> 11:43.112
Oh, my God.
What're you
doing here?

11:44.621 --> 11:46.157
Put the gun down.

11:46.248 --> 11:48.079
Not till you tell me
what the hell
you're doing here!

11:48.166 --> 11:51.078
I wanna know what
you're doing inside
Molly Walker's dreams.

11:51.169 --> 11:52.204
Who?
And what do you know

11:52.296 --> 11:54.036
about Kaito Nakamura's
murder?

11:54.131 --> 11:57.294
And while we're at it,
why is Angela Petrelli
protecting you?

11:57.551 --> 11:58.836
(SCREAMS)

11:58.927 --> 12:00.963
Wait.
What are you?
A cop?

12:01.054 --> 12:03.340
Right now I'm not.
So you better start talking.

12:03.432 --> 12:05.047
(GUN COCKING)

12:05.517 --> 12:07.132
I'm good.

12:07.227 --> 12:08.603
You've got it all wrong.

12:08.687 --> 12:11.224
Is that why
you're swinging
a shotgun?

12:11.315 --> 12:13.977
Because of that.
On the desk.

12:21.575 --> 12:23.782
They're gonna
kill me, too.

12:33.503 --> 12:36.586
Tell me about Molly Walker.
She's seen this symbol.
She's seen you.

12:36.673 --> 12:37.753
And she calls you
the nightmare man.

12:37.841 --> 12:38.956
She's looking for me.
Yeah.

12:39.051 --> 12:40.916
And she saw you
looking back at her,
and now she won't wake up.

12:41.011 --> 12:42.251
So, whatever you did,
undo it now.

12:42.346 --> 12:44.507
I'm sorry.
I'm protecting myself.

12:44.598 --> 12:46.134
Protecting yourself
from who?

12:46.224 --> 12:48.510
Which one
of her kids
are you?

12:48.602 --> 12:50.638
You're
the politician,
right?

12:50.729 --> 12:53.436
My mother is sitting in jail
for Kaito's murder.

12:53.523 --> 12:58.017
They both received
similar threats, both taken
from the same picture.

12:58.111 --> 13:01.069
The same photograph.
You were all connected.

13:01.156 --> 13:04.774
Your folks,
Kaito,
Linderman, me...

13:04.868 --> 13:08.452
We found each other.
Years ago. We thought
we could help people.

13:08.538 --> 13:09.789
Save the world.

13:09.873 --> 13:13.365
The only thing
you've ever wanted
to save is your own ass.

13:14.962 --> 13:17.044
Still angry, huh, Matt?

13:17.589 --> 13:20.251
You feel better slapping
cuffs on your dad,
make you feel good?

13:20.342 --> 13:22.549
Oh, it's starting to. Yeah.

13:23.971 --> 13:25.552
This is a waste of time.

13:25.722 --> 13:27.678
Just read his mind
so we can get
the hell out of here.

13:27.766 --> 13:29.848
MAURY: What did you say?

13:30.727 --> 13:33.469
You can read minds?

13:35.023 --> 13:38.060
(CHUCKLING)
Yeah, go ahead.

13:39.569 --> 13:41.651
Go on.

13:51.623 --> 13:53.579
(BOTH EXCLAIM IN PAIN)

13:54.960 --> 13:57.167
lt's painful, isn't it?

13:57.254 --> 13:58.585
How do you know that?

13:58.672 --> 13:59.878
Can you read minds, too?

13:59.965 --> 14:03.674
You see, Matt,
you and |, we're not
so different after all.

14:03.760 --> 14:06.251
Come on.
Unlock these cuffs.

14:07.389 --> 14:11.098
I'll tell you
everything I know.
I promise.

14:12.102 --> 14:13.933
(PLAYING CLASSICAL MUSIC)

14:23.655 --> 14:26.112
Isn't it wonderful?

14:26.199 --> 14:29.111
We've got a musician
in the house again.

14:43.925 --> 14:46.416
Nobody's touched
that thing since
my mother died.

14:46.511 --> 14:49.093
Oh. I'm sorry.
Nana said I could.

14:49.181 --> 14:53.470
But if...
Oh, yeah. It's okay.
Please, keep playing.

14:58.815 --> 15:01.272
You must really
miss your mom.

15:01.860 --> 15:03.816
Yeah. I do.

15:03.904 --> 15:05.064
I miss mine, too.

15:06.364 --> 15:10.482
I'm sure she's fine
and missing you right back.

15:13.622 --> 15:15.704
She wouldn't even tell me
where she was going.

15:15.791 --> 15:18.749
You gotta remember
she cares about you.

15:18.835 --> 15:21.497
I know new things
can be scary.

15:21.588 --> 15:26.298
My mom always said,
God doesn't give us
anything we can't handle.

15:32.641 --> 15:34.006
You play piano, too?

15:34.101 --> 15:36.592
No. Never learned.

15:50.033 --> 15:51.694
(GASPING)

15:54.204 --> 15:57.162
If you don't play,
then what was that?

16:03.964 --> 16:04.999
MR. BENNET ON PHONE.‘ Yes.

16:05.090 --> 16:07.752
I've been trying
to reach you for hours.
Where have you been?

16:07.843 --> 16:09.253
I’m at work. Why?

16:09.344 --> 16:12.507
MOH/NDER: It’s Molly.
She won’t wake up, and
her vita/s are getting worse.

16:12.597 --> 16:14.258
I'm running out
of options here.

16:14.349 --> 16:15.805
Take her to
the hospital.

16:15.892 --> 16:16.881
And say what?

16:16.977 --> 16:20.720
That she's trapped
in a nightmare? No, I'm
taking her in to the Company.

16:20.814 --> 16:22.395
MR. BENNE T:
You can’t be serious.

16:22.566 --> 16:24.306
These are the people
we're fighting against.

16:24.442 --> 16:25.978
Molly won't last,
not like this.

16:26.069 --> 16:28.401
They are the only people
who can understand
what's happening to her.

16:28.488 --> 16:30.399
Don't do this.

16:30.490 --> 16:33.357
The moment you
trust them with
what you care about most,

16:33.451 --> 16:35.362
they'll have you.

16:35.453 --> 16:38.069
Don't forget
whose side you're on.

16:38.165 --> 16:40.247
I'm on her side.

16:44.796 --> 16:46.832
MATT: All right,
you're going to
tell us everything.

16:46.923 --> 16:49.084
Every crime.
Everyone you've
ever worked with.

16:49.176 --> 16:50.336
Everything.

16:50.427 --> 16:54.170
I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry I left you.
It wasn't easy for me.

16:54.264 --> 16:56.300
Don't.
I need to say it.

16:56.391 --> 16:59.508
When I found out I could
read minds, it was
a temptation. l was weak.

16:59.603 --> 17:02.185
| used people.
l was a real scumbag.

17:02.272 --> 17:03.887
You...

17:03.982 --> 17:06.018
A cop. I'm so proud.

17:06.109 --> 17:07.645
You don't get to be proud.
You don't get to be anything.

17:07.736 --> 17:08.942
Just answer the questions.

17:09.029 --> 17:11.941
You said you tried
to save the world.

17:12.032 --> 17:13.112
How?

17:13.200 --> 17:14.610
These gifts came
out of nowhere.

17:14.743 --> 17:18.281
We just found each other,
like we were
connected somehow.

17:18.455 --> 17:21.447
We thought we were
invincible. A few of us
took that to heart.

17:21.541 --> 17:23.042
They started to do
whatever they wanted.

17:23.126 --> 17:24.707
I did what I could
to stop them.

17:24.794 --> 17:26.125
Like what?

17:26.755 --> 17:28.541
This thing
we can do,
you and l.

17:28.632 --> 17:33.626
(CHUCKLES) It only begins
at reading minds, and then
it becomes so much more.

17:34.429 --> 17:35.794
More? How?

17:35.889 --> 17:37.971
I can't explain it.

17:38.808 --> 17:43.268
No. Hang on.
I got something
I can show you

17:43.355 --> 17:45.061
'cause it helped me
understand it. Here.

17:45.148 --> 17:48.390
I've got a bunch of stuff
from back then. It's in here.

17:48.485 --> 17:50.476
(CHUCKLES) Oh, come on.

18:01.831 --> 18:03.867
Matt!

18:05.961 --> 18:07.997
Matt!

18:09.714 --> 18:11.045
MATT: Dad!

18:11.132 --> 18:13.214
What's going on?

18:14.844 --> 18:16.459
(DISTORTED)

18:17.389 --> 18:19.550
Hey. What the hell's
going on?

18:19.641 --> 18:21.802
Where am |?

18:22.185 --> 18:24.096
(DISTORTED
CHATTERING)

18:42.455 --> 18:44.616
This is impossible.

18:45.542 --> 18:47.624
We saved this city.

18:54.467 --> 18:58.051
Let me out! It's a mistake.
I'm not supposed to be here.

18:58.555 --> 19:01.092
Yeah. No one's
supposed to be here.

19:03.852 --> 19:05.968
Pleasant dreams.

19:37.927 --> 19:40.179
(SCIENTIST SPEAKING JAPANESE)

19:49.564 --> 19:51.304
(AN DO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

20:06.748 --> 20:07.737
(CHUCKLES)

20:28.853 --> 20:30.434
(GASPS)

20:31.356 --> 20:33.392
(H/RO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

20:36.486 --> 20:38.067
(CHUCKLES)

20:38.154 --> 20:40.145
(H/RO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

21:07.016 --> 21:08.847
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

21:13.940 --> 21:15.771
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

21:24.117 --> 21:26.153
(HIRO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

21:41.134 --> 21:43.170
Monica.

21:44.179 --> 21:47.091
I think I know
what happened
with the piano.

21:47.640 --> 21:50.973
What can I say?
Guess I'm just
a musical genius.

21:51.060 --> 21:53.437
Or it's something else.

21:56.065 --> 21:57.054
(SIGHING)

21:57.150 --> 22:00.608
Look, it's been
a hard couple days
for me.

22:01.404 --> 22:03.395
In fact,
it's been a hard
couple years.

22:03.490 --> 22:08.450
So I think I'm just
gonna take a nice
long nap and sleep it off.

22:08.578 --> 22:10.660
Monica.

22:12.749 --> 22:16.162
You remember last night
when I said I was able to rig
the Pay-Per-View on the TV?

22:16.252 --> 22:18.243
Yeah.

22:21.049 --> 22:24.962
MAN ON TV: ...construction
for the rebuilding of downtown
New Orleans is in full swing.

22:25.053 --> 22:27.385
People are returning
and looking for a fresh start.

22:27.472 --> 22:30.088
Restaurants
and retail stores...

22:32.560 --> 22:34.596
Well, I lied.

22:35.104 --> 22:37.140
HOW did...

22:37.941 --> 22:40.023
How did you...

22:40.109 --> 22:42.361
I think it runs
in the family.

22:44.030 --> 22:47.318
I mean,
maybe not
exactly like me,

22:48.618 --> 22:50.950
but my dad could
walk through walls.

22:51.788 --> 22:53.699
D.L.?

22:53.790 --> 22:54.825
Yeah.

22:54.916 --> 22:56.952
And my mom...

22:57.460 --> 22:59.872
Don't even get me
started on my mom.

22:59.963 --> 23:03.501
But I think what's going on
with you is more like this.

23:06.803 --> 23:09.010
A comic book?
Yeah.

23:09.806 --> 23:12.548
This is St. Joan.
She's a muscle mimic.

23:12.642 --> 23:13.882
A What?

23:13.977 --> 23:15.183
A copycat.

23:15.270 --> 23:17.511
Whatever she sees,
she can do.

23:19.148 --> 23:22.436
That's just like
what you did with
me and the piano.

23:25.822 --> 23:27.904
Copycat.

23:30.910 --> 23:32.992
Copycat.

23:34.247 --> 23:35.987
Look at this.

23:36.082 --> 23:40.416
I shouldn't know
how to do this.
I saw it on TV.

23:43.089 --> 23:45.171
Oh, my God.

23:45.967 --> 23:50.301
So if this is really
happening to you, maybe
we ought to go test it out.

24:00.857 --> 24:01.972
(SIGHING)

24:02.066 --> 24:03.442
I didn't know
where else to go.

24:03.526 --> 24:04.891
Oh, you made
the right choice.

24:04.986 --> 24:08.524
We're going to do
everything we can
for Molly.

24:08.615 --> 24:10.321
In the meantime,

24:10.408 --> 24:14.151
we have someone else
who needs us, and we would
like you to bring her in.

24:14.370 --> 24:16.235
You're sending
me into the field?
Yes.

24:16.331 --> 24:18.117
Molly needs me here.
No,no,no.

24:18.207 --> 24:20.368
Molly is our
top priority here,

24:20.460 --> 24:22.576
but we need you out there
doing the good work you do,

24:22.670 --> 24:24.786
helping others like her.

24:24.881 --> 24:27.463
And you're
gonna need this.

24:29.969 --> 24:33.382
This is how
you help people?
By tasering them?

24:33.473 --> 24:37.557
Well, that's just
standard procedure to
make sure everyone's safe.

24:37.727 --> 24:41.140
A lot of the people
we encounter aren't in
control of their abilities.

24:41.230 --> 24:44.597
Trust me. It's easier
to ask forgiveness
than permission.

24:44.692 --> 24:46.478
MAN 1: Niki's loose!

24:46.569 --> 24:47.684
MAN 2: Grab her.

24:47.779 --> 24:49.815
MAN 3: Get her!

24:49.906 --> 24:51.396
Niki?

24:52.408 --> 24:53.818
(GRUNTS)

24:53.910 --> 24:55.525
(ALARM SOUNDING)

24:57.789 --> 24:59.245
(GASPING)

25:02.085 --> 25:03.040
(SHOT FIRES)

25:03.127 --> 25:04.458
(GROANS)

25:12.428 --> 25:14.805
What the hell
is going on here?

25:22.939 --> 25:24.725
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

25:25.441 --> 25:29.150
So do you wanna try
something really rad,
like a kick flip?

25:32.782 --> 25:34.773
Slam dunk?

25:35.076 --> 25:36.691
(MEN EXCLAIMING)

25:38.705 --> 25:40.036
(GIRLS CHATTERING)

25:40.123 --> 25:43.957
Well, I always
sucked at Double Dutch.

25:48.381 --> 25:50.417
You want
something, lady?

26:00.059 --> 26:02.596
Yeah. lwannajump in.

26:06.232 --> 26:08.314
And don't call me lady.

26:16.659 --> 26:17.899
(GIRLS CHEERING)

26:27.503 --> 26:28.879
(LAUGHING)

26:37.430 --> 26:39.136
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

26:39.640 --> 26:40.971
It's not much.

26:41.058 --> 26:43.310
I sleep in a pub,
remember?

26:51.152 --> 26:53.188
You paint?

26:53.446 --> 26:55.482
It's what I do
to relax.

26:56.407 --> 26:58.443
These are amazing.

27:03.372 --> 27:04.578
You're talented.

27:04.665 --> 27:08.533
Is that why you kidnapped me,
so you could sort through
me things?

27:08.628 --> 27:11.586
Don't start liking me less
now that you're peeling
away the mystery.

27:11.672 --> 27:13.208
| just...

27:13.299 --> 27:15.585
I wanted to see
where you lived.

27:16.093 --> 27:18.300
Lie on a real bed, maybe.

27:18.387 --> 27:20.423
No one's
stopping you.

27:25.686 --> 27:27.472
What are you
looking at?

27:27.563 --> 27:28.643
Nothing.

27:29.649 --> 27:31.856
Then what is it
that's on your mind?

27:31.943 --> 27:33.103
You were right.

27:40.117 --> 27:42.779
Whatever I was,
whoever I am,

27:44.247 --> 27:46.363
l have to face it.

27:51.295 --> 27:54.537
Nothing that | find
in this box is gonna
change anything.

27:54.757 --> 27:56.213
Whatever my life
was before,

27:56.300 --> 27:59.758
this is where I want
to be now. With you.

28:00.805 --> 28:02.511
Okay?

28:02.598 --> 28:05.135
Okay. Get on
with it, then.

28:17.029 --> 28:19.111
Peter Petrelli?

28:21.284 --> 28:23.320
I'm from New York.

28:24.704 --> 28:26.865
Looks like you were leaving.
This is an open ticket.

28:26.956 --> 28:29.038
New York to Montreal.

28:32.795 --> 28:34.331
Who's that?

28:34.422 --> 28:35.582
| wish I knew.

28:37.049 --> 28:41.008
None of this tells me
how I got here or
what I'm supposed to do.

28:51.647 --> 28:53.683
What is it?

29:01.991 --> 29:04.073
Peter?

29:08.873 --> 29:10.989
My God. Peter.

29:31.854 --> 29:34.766
You know, I've never been
in an Irish pub before.

29:34.857 --> 29:37.098
Do you have Haggis?

29:37.193 --> 29:41.687
That's Scotland, love.
We have stew, and mussels,

29:42.114 --> 29:43.615
and stew.

29:43.699 --> 29:44.950
But I'm closing up.

29:45.034 --> 29:47.195
Oh. Well...

29:47.703 --> 29:50.080
Yeah, lwas hoping
you could help me.

29:50.164 --> 29:52.029
I'm looking for a guy.

29:52.124 --> 29:54.831
Best time for
that's right after
a football match.

29:54.919 --> 29:58.411
Fellas are locked out
of their minds.
Up for anything.

29:59.256 --> 30:00.587
(LAUGHS)

30:01.217 --> 30:03.208
His name's
Peter Petrelli.

30:04.595 --> 30:06.677
Never seen him before.

30:08.015 --> 30:10.097
Never seen him before?

30:11.060 --> 30:13.051
No.

30:14.855 --> 30:16.891
Cool. Thanks.

30:23.239 --> 30:25.400
The thing is,

30:25.491 --> 30:29.985
I talked to a few people
from the docks. They said
they saw him in here.

30:31.622 --> 30:33.829
I don't know
what to tell you.

30:34.417 --> 30:35.406
Hmm.

30:35.501 --> 30:39.244
So either you're lying,
or all those other people
are lying.

30:39.880 --> 30:43.247
It's just kind of hard
to tell who's lying,
you know?

30:45.094 --> 30:48.552
Like I said,
I don't know
this Peter.

30:49.807 --> 30:51.843
That it, now?

30:56.147 --> 30:58.229
I guess so.

31:02.278 --> 31:05.020
Sorry I couldn't
be more help.

31:05.114 --> 31:07.150
Yeah.

31:07.700 --> 31:09.782
So am I.

31:21.338 --> 31:23.875
You gave us quite a scare.

31:24.633 --> 31:26.624
I'm sorry about earlier.

31:27.636 --> 31:29.797
I'm feeling
much better now.

31:29.889 --> 31:31.095
Thank you.

31:31.182 --> 31:33.264
Well, we knew
it wouldn't be easy.

31:33.350 --> 31:36.217
Multiple-personality disorder
is a terrible affliction.

31:36.312 --> 31:39.975
But we're gonna get you
well again. I promise.

31:40.816 --> 31:42.852
Thank you.

31:51.368 --> 31:52.403
I'm going
to get you
out of here.

31:52.495 --> 31:53.530
lcantleave.

31:53.621 --> 31:55.077
Niki, you're a prisoner.

31:55.164 --> 31:57.029
(SCOFFS) No, I'm not.

31:58.125 --> 32:02.084
I came here on my own.
I gave up my son to be here.

32:03.547 --> 32:05.583
I'm sick.

32:08.469 --> 32:12.053
I didn't think anyone
could ever understand
my problems.

32:12.681 --> 32:14.808
What I've done,

32:14.892 --> 32:16.723
what I'm capable of.

32:19.021 --> 32:22.013
These are the only people
that can help me.

32:39.125 --> 32:41.161
MAN: (WHISPERING) Nathan!

32:42.795 --> 32:44.831
Peter?

32:47.216 --> 32:48.296
Peter.

32:48.384 --> 32:49.965
Peter, I knew it.

32:50.052 --> 32:52.384
I knew you could survive.

32:52.471 --> 32:54.507
You?

32:56.600 --> 32:58.465
You can't run
from me, Nathan.

32:59.186 --> 33:00.767
(BABY CRYING)

33:04.984 --> 33:06.690
There's a baby.

33:06.777 --> 33:09.735
Hey! You gotta
get this baby
out of here.

33:10.197 --> 33:11.653
(SHOUTING)

33:17.413 --> 33:20.280
Janice? What are you
doing in here?

33:21.792 --> 33:25.626
Is that... Janice,
is that baby mine?

33:25.713 --> 33:27.453
(CONTINUES CRYING)

33:27.548 --> 33:29.254
You said
I wasn't
the father.

33:29.341 --> 33:30.956
But you read minds.

33:31.594 --> 33:35.462
You looked into my head
and you saw the truth
but you still left.

33:35.556 --> 33:38.343
No. No, I didn't!
I didn't know!

33:39.268 --> 33:40.974
You left him.

33:41.061 --> 33:45.270
Just like your father
left you. Just like
you're gonna leave Molly.

33:47.151 --> 33:49.563
No. No, Janice.

33:50.487 --> 33:52.694
Janice! Hey!

33:54.116 --> 33:55.356
(GRUNTING)

33:55.451 --> 33:58.818
You're no hero.
Everybody's dead
because of you.

33:58.913 --> 33:59.902
We have to stop it.

33:59.997 --> 34:02.739
You can't.
You don't want
redemption.

34:02.833 --> 34:04.869
You want ignorance.

34:06.045 --> 34:09.333
Let's go to the edge.
You won't feel anything.

34:10.174 --> 34:12.665
You never do.

34:12.760 --> 34:13.920
You don't know me.

34:14.011 --> 34:16.047
lam you.

34:16.138 --> 34:17.423
(GROANS)

34:18.933 --> 34:20.548
(MATT SCREAMING)

34:23.979 --> 34:25.389
(GRUNTING)

34:25.981 --> 34:27.312
(GROANS)

34:31.320 --> 34:32.810
(GRUNTING)

34:48.504 --> 34:50.040
(EVIL LAUGHTER)

34:52.341 --> 34:54.423
(GASPING) Stop. Nathan.

34:54.885 --> 34:56.921
Nathan, wake up.

34:57.554 --> 34:59.055
(GRUNTING)

34:59.139 --> 35:02.631
Nathan. Wake up.
Wake up. Nathan.

35:02.726 --> 35:06.014
Nathan.
Wake up.
Wake up.

35:19.034 --> 35:20.114
What happened?

35:20.202 --> 35:22.113
Now we know
why Molly calls him
the nightmare man.

35:22.204 --> 35:25.788
You stopped it.
How did you do that?

35:29.169 --> 35:30.158
(GRUNTING)

35:30.254 --> 35:32.290
I don't know.

35:33.590 --> 35:35.626
He's gone.

35:36.427 --> 35:38.509
What are you looking for?

35:39.555 --> 35:41.295
We need to know
where he went.

35:41.390 --> 35:43.631
Why he's doing this.
Something to...

35:43.726 --> 35:45.808
What?

35:46.228 --> 35:49.561
I knew this was a con.
I knew I couldn't trust him.

36:00.826 --> 36:03.283
NATHAN: I think I know
where he's headed.

36:05.581 --> 36:08.448
That's Bob.
He's one of them.

36:09.918 --> 36:11.203
He runs the Company.

36:11.295 --> 36:14.287
Not for long.
Looks like he's next.

36:19.094 --> 36:21.130
(HIRO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

36:31.273 --> 36:34.231
KENSEI: According to the map,
White Beard's camp should
be right over this ridge.

36:34.318 --> 36:36.229
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

36:39.990 --> 36:41.776
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

36:48.957 --> 36:50.948
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

36:55.839 --> 36:57.704
(SOLDIERS CHATTERING)

36:58.967 --> 37:00.503
(MAN SHOUTING)

37:03.514 --> 37:06.176
Right after
we defeat
his entire army.

37:06.892 --> 37:08.302
(GULPING)

37:08.394 --> 37:10.476
(HIRO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

37:21.281 --> 37:23.021
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

37:28.872 --> 37:31.124
(SCIENTIST SPEAKING JAPANESE)

37:45.681 --> 37:47.012
(EXCLAIMS)

37:49.268 --> 37:51.350
MAN ON TV:
The fire started
around 8:00.

37:53.647 --> 37:55.512
(MEN SHOUT/NG ON TV)

37:59.862 --> 38:01.272
(GRUNTS)

38:09.746 --> 38:11.156
(GRUNTING)

38:16.211 --> 38:18.202
(LAUGHS)
That is amazing.

38:19.631 --> 38:21.496
Yeah.

38:21.592 --> 38:23.503
I know.

38:23.594 --> 38:28.429
But what do you think
it all means?
Having these... These powers.

38:28.515 --> 38:30.221
I think it means
that we're special.

38:30.309 --> 38:31.549
But why?

38:31.727 --> 38:36.642
I mean, all this time
I've been praying
to God to give me direction.

38:36.732 --> 38:40.224
To show me what
I'm supposed to do
with my life.

38:41.069 --> 38:43.776
Of all the things
He could give to me...

38:44.698 --> 38:47.405
Maybe we're supposed
to do something with these.

38:49.244 --> 38:51.235
ljust wish I knew what.

38:53.457 --> 38:55.618
It is way
pastyour
